.\" Manpage for simple_shell.
.\" Contact
.TH man 1 "14 Abril 2021" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- program that emulate the UNIX shell behavior
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a program that takes commands from the keyboard and gives them
to the operating system to perform, it can be executed on interactive or
non-interactive mode.
.SH OPTIONS
The simple_shell does not take any options.
.SH INVOCATION
Compile simple_shell whit the following line:
.PP
.B gcc *.c -o ./hsh
.PP
In order to use the interactive mode execute:
.PP
.B ./hsh
.PP
And the following string indicates that you stay in the prompt:
.PP
.B #cisfun$
.PP
In order to use the non-interactive mode execute:
.PP
.B echo "[command and flags]" | ./hsh
.PP


.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
